## Listing Shifts

```shell
curl <%=@api_prefix%>/shifts/?location_id=1&start_time=2014-03-05 \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```

```json
{
  "start": "Wed, 05 Mar 2014 00:00:00 -0600",
  "end": "Sat, 08 Mar 2014 23:59:59 -0600",
  "shifts": [
    <%= partial "objects/shift_json" %>,
    {
      "id": 2,
      "location_id": 1,
      "start_time": "Wed, 06 Mar 2014 08:00:00",
      "end_time": "Wed, 06 Mar 2014 13:30:00",
      ...
      "notes": "Come in early today"
    }
  ]
}
```

This method allows you to search for shifts. See the parameters below for all the options.

### HTTP Request
`GET <%=@api_prefix%>/2/shifts`

### Parameters

Key | Description
--- | -----------
start_time | Start time for a search window
end_time | End time for a search window
user_id | Only show shifts for a user, or multiple (e.g. 1,5,3)
location_id | Only show shifts for a location, or multiple.



## Get Existing Shift

```shell
curl <%=@api_prefix%>/shifts/1 \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```

```json
{
  "shift": {
    "id": 1,
    "user_id": 1,
    "location_id": 1,
    "start_time": "Wed, 06 Mar 2014 08:00:00",
    "end_time": "Wed, 06 Mar 2014 13:30:00",
    ...
    "notes": "Come in early today"
  }
}
```

### HTTP Request
`GET <%=@api_prefix%>/2/shifts/{id}`

### Parameters

Key | Description
--- | -----------
id | ID of the shift requested.



## Create/Update Shift

### Create HTTP Request
`POST <%=@api_prefix%>/2/shifts/`

### Update HTTP Requests
`PUT <%=@api_prefix%>/2/shifts/{id}`

### Post/Put Body

Key | Description
--- | -----------
id | ID of the shift requested.




## Delete Existing Shift

```shell
curl -X DELETE <%=@api_prefix%>/shifts/1 \
 -H "W-Token: <%=@wiw_token%>"
```

```json
{
  "success": true
}
```

### HTTP Request
`DELETE <%=@api_prefix%>/2/shifts/{id}`

### Parameters

Key | Description
--- | -----------
id | ID of the shift requested.
ids | Optional query parameter that can be used to delete multiple shifts. `?ids=5,2,34`








